text.paragraph:
Onset of pseudomembranous colitis may occur during or after antibacterial treatment. (See 
                        WARNINGS
                     )  Nausea and vomiting have been reported rarely. The most frequent side effect has been diarrhea. It was very rarely severe enough to warrant cessation of therapy. Dyspepsia, gastritis, and abdominal pain have also occurred. As with some penicillins and some other cephalosporins, transient hepatitis and cholestatic jaundice have been reported rarely.
